<h1>Problem 1006 - 2018 China TST Test 2, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(M,a,b,r\) be non-negative integers with \(a,r\ge 2\), and suppose there exists a function \(f:\mathbb{Z}\rightarrow\mathbb{Z}\) satisfying the following conditions: <ol><li>For all \(n\in \mathbb{Z}\), \(f^{(r)}(n)=an+b\) where \(f^{(r)}\) denotes the composition of \(r\) copies of \(f\)</li><li>For all \(n\ge M\), \(f(n)\ge 0\)</li><li>For all \(n>m>M\), \(n-m \mid f(n)-f(m)\)</li></ol> Show that \(a\) is a perfect \(r\)-th power.</p>
